{"questionId":"9069303","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Magnesium is a reactive metal often found in alloys.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A graph of the volume of gas produced by reacting magnesium with a large excess of 1 mol dm<sup>–3</sup> hydrochloric acid is shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/c4429239f9ebee43cc426355ae742cfb7c2f9c5e.png\" width=\"507\" height=\"331\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use the graph to deduce the dependence of the reaction rate on the amount of Mg.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>independent / not dependent ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept “zero order in Mg”.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069303","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.2c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Use the graph to deduce the dependence of the reaction rate on the amount of Mg.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.2 Graphical techniques","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}